      </exercise><exercise id="fs-id2717829" type="ap-test-prep"><problem id="fs-id2263129">
          <para id="fs-id2428684">In an experiment, light is passed through two polarizing filters. The image below shows the first filter and axis of polarization.</para>
          <figure id="fs-id1481746"><media id="fs-id1866435" alt="An arrow indicates light is going from a diagram E with arrows pointing in all directions, then a Polarizing filter with a vertical arrow in one direction labeled Axis. The light diagram to the right of the filter shows only one vertical line with arrows pointing up and down.">
              <image mime-type="image/jpg" src="../../media/Figure_28_08_16a.jpg"/>
            </media>
    
          </figure><para id="fs-id1383030">The intensity of the resulting light (after the first filter) is recorded as <emphasis effect="italics">I</emphasis>. Three configurations (at different angles) are set up for the second filter, and the intensity of light is recorded for each configuration. The results are shown in the table below:</para>
